  "text": "Immunofluorescence was performed as described previously (36, [CITATION_1] . Briefly, the three cell types were subeultured on glass coverslips for 3 d in the appropriate medium. The cells then were rinsed with Dulbecco's phosphate-buffered saline (PBS), fixed for I h in PBS containing 3.7% formaldehyde and 5% sucrose, and rinsed three times with PBS over a 15-rain period. The cells then were incubated with anti-fibronectin antibodies (20 ug/ml for 1 h). Indirect immunofluoreseence was performed exactly as described before using a fluorescent second antibody (diluted l:10). Routine controls included incubating the cells with an equal concentration of preimmune IgG from the same goat or omitting the first antibody and were always negative.",
